## Spacing System

The spacing system is based on a **4px base unit** for consistent rhythm throughout the UI:

```xaml
<Thickness x:Key="SpacingXS">4</Thickness>      <!-- 4px -->
<Thickness x:Key="SpacingS">8</Thickness>       <!-- 8px -->
<Thickness x:Key="SpacingM">16</Thickness>      <!-- 16px -->
<Thickness x:Key="SpacingL">24</Thickness>      <!-- 24px -->
<Thickness x:Key="SpacingXL">32</Thickness>     <!-- 32px -->
<Thickness x:Key="SpacingXXL">48</Thickness>    <!-- 48px -->
```

Double values are also available for numeric properties:
```xaml
<sys:Double x:Key="SpacingMValue">16</sys:Double>
```

### Usage Guidelines

- **SpacingXS (4px)**: Tight spacing within components (e.g., badge padding)
- **SpacingS (8px)**: Small gaps between related items
- **SpacingM (16px)**: Standard spacing between sections, default padding
- **SpacingL (24px)**: Large spacing between major sections, card padding
- **SpacingXL (32px)**: Extra large spacing for major separations
- **SpacingXXL (48px)**: Maximum spacing for dramatic separation

### Example

```xaml
<StackPanel Margin="{StaticResource SpacingL}">
    <TextBlock Text="Title" Margin="0,0,0,{StaticResource SpacingMValue}"/>
    <TextBlock Text="Content" />
</StackPanel>
```

## Icon System

The application uses **Segoe MDL2 Assets**, a built-in Windows font containing icons. This eliminates the need for external icon libraries.

### Icon Glyphs

Icons are defined as Unicode string resources:

```xaml
<sys:String x:Key="Icon.Play">&#xE768;</sys:String>
<sys:String x:Key="Icon.Stop">&#xE71A;</sys:String>
<sys:String x:Key="Icon.Refresh">&#xE72C;</sys:String>
<sys:String x:Key="Icon.Home">&#xE80F;</sys:String>
<sys:String x:Key="Icon.Settings">&#xE713;</sys:String>
<!-- ... and many more -->
```

### Icon Style

The base icon style sets the Segoe MDL2 Assets font:

```xaml
<Style x:Key="Icon" TargetType="TextBlock">
    <Setter Property="FontFamily" Value="Segoe MDL2 Assets"/>
    <Setter Property="FontSize" Value="16"/>
    <Setter Property="VerticalAlignment" Value="Center"/>
    <Setter Property="HorizontalAlignment" Value="Center"/>
</Style>
```

### Using Icons

Icons are displayed using `TextBlock` with the Icon style:

```xaml
<!-- Basic icon -->
<TextBlock Text="{StaticResource Icon.Play}" Style="{StaticResource Icon}"/>

<!-- Icon with custom size and color -->
<TextBlock Text="{StaticResource Icon.Refresh}"
           Style="{StaticResource Icon}"
           Width="24"
           Height="24"
           FontSize="24"
           Foreground="{StaticResource PrimaryBrush}"/>

<!-- Icon in a button -->
<Button Style="{StaticResource PrimaryButton}">
    <StackPanel Orientation="Horizontal">
        <TextBlock Text="{StaticResource Icon.Play}"
                   Style="{StaticResource Icon}"
                   Foreground="White"
                   Margin="0,0,8,0"/>
        <TextBlock Text="Start Crawl" Foreground="White"/>
