                    <DoubleAnimation Storyboard.TargetProperty="(UIElement.RenderTransform).(RotateTransform.Angle)"
                                     From="0" To="360" Duration="0:0:2"
                                     RepeatBehavior="Forever"/>
                </Storyboard>
            </BeginStoryboard>
        </EventTrigger>
    </TextBlock.Triggers>
</TextBlock>
```

## Best Practices

### 1. Always Use Static Resources

```xaml
<!-- ✓ Correct -->
<TextBlock Foreground="{StaticResource TextPrimaryBrush}"/>
<Button Style="{StaticResource PrimaryButton}"/>

<!-- ✗ Incorrect -->
<TextBlock Foreground="#1F1F1F"/>
<Button Background="#0078D4" Foreground="White"/>
```

### 2. Use Spacing Constants

```xaml
<!-- ✓ Correct -->
<StackPanel Margin="{StaticResource SpacingL}"/>

<!-- ✗ Incorrect -->
<StackPanel Margin="24"/>
```

### 3. Icons in Buttons Need Explicit Foreground

```xaml
<!-- ✓ Correct -->
<Button Style="{StaticResource PrimaryButton}">
    <StackPanel Orientation="Horizontal">
        <TextBlock Text="{StaticResource Icon.Play}"
                   Style="{StaticResource Icon}"
                   Foreground="White"/>
        <TextBlock Text="Play" Foreground="White"/>
    </StackPanel>
</Button>

<!-- ✗ Incorrect - Icons will be dark instead of white -->
<Button Style="{StaticResource PrimaryButton}">
    <StackPanel Orientation="Horizontal">
        <TextBlock Text="{StaticResource Icon.Play}" Style="{StaticResource Icon}"/>
        <TextBlock Text="Play"/>
    </StackPanel>
</Button>
```

### 4. TextBox Placeholders Use Tag Property

```xaml
<!-- ✓ Correct -->
<TextBox Tag="Enter your name" Style="{StaticResource StandardTextBox}"/>

<!-- ✗ Incorrect - md:HintAssist no longer exists -->
<TextBox md:HintAssist.Hint="Enter your name"/>
```

### 5. Cards Use Border, Not Custom Controls

```xaml
<!-- ✓ Correct -->
<Border Style="{StaticResource Card}">
    <!-- Content -->
</Border>

<!-- ✗ Incorrect - md:Card no longer exists -->
<md:Card>
    <!-- Content -->
</md:Card>
```

### 6. Inherit TabItem Style When Customizing

```xaml
<!-- ✓ Correct -->
<TabControl.ItemContainerStyle>
    <Style TargetType="TabItem" BasedOn="{StaticResource {x:Type TabItem}}">
        <Setter Property="Height" Value="48"/>
    </Style>
</TabControl.ItemContainerStyle>

<!-- ✗ Incorrect - Will lose custom styling -->
<TabControl.ItemContainerStyle>
    <Style TargetType="TabItem">
        <Setter Property="Height" Value="48"/>
    </Style>
</TabControl.ItemContainerStyle>
```

## Adding New Styles

When adding new styles to the application:

1. **Define in Styles.xaml**: All styles must be added to `src/ShoutingIguana/Styles/Styles.xaml`
2. **Follow Naming Convention**: Use PascalCase with descriptive names (e.g., `PrimaryButton`, `MetricCard`)
3. **Use Existing Resources**: Build on existing color and spacing resources
4. **Add Documentation**: Add XML comments explaining the style's purpose and usage
5. **Maintain Consistency**: Follow the established patterns for similar controls

Example:

```xaml
<!-- ========================================
     CUSTOM CONTROL STYLES
     ======================================== -->

<!-- Usage: <Border Style="{StaticResource CustomCard}"/> -->
<Style x:Key="CustomCard" TargetType="Border" BasedOn="{StaticResource Card}">
    <Setter Property="BorderBrush" Value="{StaticResource PrimaryBrush}"/>
    <Setter Property="BorderThickness" Value="2"/>
    <Setter Property="Padding" Value="16"/>
</Style>
```

## Troubleshooting

### Problem: Icons Not Showing

**Solution**: Ensure you're using the correct icon key and the Icon style:
```xaml
<TextBlock Text="{StaticResource Icon.Play}" Style="{StaticResource Icon}"/>
```

### Problem: TabControl Looks Wrong

**Solution**: Use the StandardTabControl style and inherit TabItem style when customizing:
```xaml
<TabControl Style="{StaticResource StandardTabControl}">
    <TabControl.ItemContainerStyle>
        <Style TargetType="TabItem" BasedOn="{StaticResource {x:Type TabItem}}">
            <!-- Customizations -->
        </Style>
    </TabControl.ItemContainerStyle>
</TabControl>
```

### Problem: TextBox Placeholder Not Showing

**Solution**: Set the placeholder text using the `Tag` property:
```xaml
<TextBox Tag="Your placeholder text" Style="{StaticResource StandardTextBox}"/>
```

### Problem: Button Icons Are Dark Instead of White

**Solution**: Explicitly set `Foreground="White"` on icons inside Primary/Danger buttons:
```xaml
<Button Style="{StaticResource PrimaryButton}">
    <TextBlock Text="{StaticResource Icon.Play}"
               Style="{StaticResource Icon}"
               Foreground="White"/>
</Button>
```

